Self-consistency prompting is asking an AI to solve the same problem a few different ways, then choosing the answer that comes up the most often. For example, if you ask an AI a tricky math riddle, you can tell it to show three different ways to solve it. If the AI gets "15" using the first method, "12" using the second method, and "15" using the third method, it picks "15" as the final answer because that result was the most consistent.
